Osun State government has appointed a tax consultant, Bicci Alli, as acting head of Osun Internal Revenue Service (OIRS). Alli, who possesses degrees in business administration, accounting and other qualifications in taxation, is a fellow of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria (ICAN) and the Chartered Institute of Taxation of Nigeria (CITN), according to a statement. Formerly of the Lagos State Internal Revenue Service (LIRS), Alli has presented over 50 papers on various aspects of tax policies, laws and administration at different fora, locally and internationally.